message.text:
BREAKING: Only preschool and kindergarten classes in all public and private schools in the City of Manila are suspended tomorrow, December 2, 2019 due to Typhoon Tisoy.

This after state weather bureau PAGASA placed Metro Manila under Signal No. 1.

###

BACKGROUND: Based on the Department Order No. 43, series of 2012 of the Department of Education, "When Signal No. 1 is raised by PAGASA, public and private preschool and kindergarten classes in the affected areas shall be automatically cancelled or suspended." 

###

EARLIER: Manila City Mayor Francisco “Isko Moreno” Domagoso suspended classes in the following schools from December 2 to 7, 2019 in view of the 30th SEA Games.

-Pamantasan ng Lungsod ng Maynila
-Universidad de Manila
-Aurora Quezon Elementary School
